    "en": {
      "title": "The demand of United People's Power",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The United People's Shakti has demanded the release of the arrested student activists.",
        "The United People's Power announced in a statement that the government, which had declared that it would not put any obstacles in peaceful protests, has suppressed the constitution, accountability and democracy in accordance with international law, through the use of emergency law.",
        "General Secretary of United People's Shakti Ranjith Mathuma Bandara has said that the contradictions between President's opinion and actions are evident by the fact that the President has announced that the Emergency Act will be lifted, through a special gazette announcement, and the fact that three soldiers have been called to 07 districts. (a)"
